11:55.315 --> 11:57.282
Doesn't matter what party
you're from.

11:57.284 --> 11:59.718
All of us women have to break
through the same glass ceiling.
(laughter)

11:59.720 --> 12:03.154
Give any piece of trailer trash
a push-up bra and a microphone,

12:03.156 --> 12:06.491
And those stupid flyovers will
eat it up like fried twinkies--
mellie...

12:06.493 --> 12:08.159
My mic's still on.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.961
(projector and camera shutter
click)

12:12.898 --> 12:14.065
(gasps)

12:14.067 --> 12:16.201
(projector and camera shutter
click)

12:16.203 --> 12:18.002
<i>Our daughter was</i>
<i>a kind, generous person.</i>

12:18.004 --> 12:21.206
<i>Every day she made us proud</i>
<i>to be her parents.</i>

12:21.208 --> 12:23.341
<i>She's dead. The things</i>
<i>these people are saying--</i>

12:23.343 --> 12:25.276
<i>They should be ashamed.</i>
<i>Turn it off.</i>

12:25.278 --> 12:28.046
Tomorrow's all about
prepping the senator's wife.

12:28.048 --> 12:29.214
This entire case hangs

12:29.216 --> 12:32.884
I don't want any surprises
up on the stand.
We're on it.

12:42.862 --> 12:44.028
Huck.

12:45.798 --> 12:48.199
I was worried about you, okay?

12:48.201 --> 12:49.834
Why?
What?

12:49.836 --> 12:52.804
Why are you worried about me?
I come to work. I do my job.

12:52.806 --> 12:55.774
I go home. I have appropriate
emotional responses,

12:55.776 --> 12:58.109
And I'm taking social cues
for behavior.

12:58.111 --> 13:00.745
I am being normal.
Why are you worried?

13:00.747 --> 13:01.813
You're not...

13:01.815 --> 13:03.782
You're not talking to me,

13:03.784 --> 13:05.784
Not like you used to.
We're not...

13:05.786 --> 13:09.554
Look, I wanted to know
what was up.
So you followed me.

13:09.556 --> 13:12.157
Yeah.
Friends don't follow friends.

13:12.159 --> 13:13.992
I'm not a client, quinn.
You don't fix me.

13:13.994 --> 13:16.194
But those meetings do?
Those meetings are
supposed to be anonymous.

13:16.196 --> 13:18.263
They're also supposed to be
for alcoholics.

13:18.265 --> 13:20.865
Well... (sighs) huck, wait.
Who did you--

13:20.867 --> 13:22.834
You said you drank
the whiskey.

13:24.236 --> 13:26.571
That's a person, right?

13:26.573 --> 13:29.507
You killed someone
and it felt good?

13:29.509 --> 13:31.276
Like a high?

13:43.155 --> 13:44.589
(guns clink)

13:44.591 --> 13:46.524
What do you want?
To talk.

13:50.029 --> 13:52.030
What do you want?
To talk.

13:52.032 --> 13:54.332
I don't know what
you're talking about.

13:54.334 --> 13:58.536
I think you wanna take him out
as much as I do.

13:58.538 --> 14:01.039
(cocks gun)
we're both wearing leashes,
huck.

14:01.041 --> 14:03.541
You and me and everyone else
who's ever worked for that man--

14:03.543 --> 14:07.979
He owns us,
just like he owns liv.

14:07.981 --> 14:09.314
But if we could get
something on him--

14:09.316 --> 14:11.883
Something big like
murdering a guy--
no.

14:11.885 --> 14:13.985
Why?
Because no one takes down
command.

14:13.987 --> 14:15.887
No one's ever tried.
Stay away from liv.

14:15.889 --> 14:18.223
Stay away from me.

14:18.225 --> 14:20.091
(gun clicks)

14:24.496 --> 14:26.097
"worst lady"!

14:26.099 --> 14:28.366
(newspaper rustling)
"first catty bares claws"!

14:28.368 --> 14:29.634
"mouthy mellie"--

14:29.636 --> 14:31.169
"first catty"?
That doesn't even rhyme.

14:31.171 --> 14:32.203
What's the second rule
of politics?

14:32.205 --> 14:34.239
I know the damn rules.

14:34.241 --> 14:36.875
The same rule applies
to gun ownership.

14:36.877 --> 14:38.309
The microphone
is always loaded!

14:38.311 --> 14:39.944
I know the rules.
I took my mic off.

14:39.946 --> 14:41.579
Blame that
stupid congresswoman.
I'd like to,

14:41.581 --> 14:43.214
But then you had to go
and break rule number one--

14:43.216 --> 14:45.183
Never insult the voters.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.318
It'll blow over.
I will make it right.

14:47.320 --> 14:51.222
Josephine marcus went
from flavor of the month

14:51.224 --> 14:53.391
To legitimate
presidential candidate.

14:53.393 --> 14:55.193
You did that.
<i>You</i> gave her legitimacy.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.295
You minted her ass!

14:57.297 --> 14:58.897
Even better.
She's inexperienced.

14:58.899 --> 15:01.966
So that we can crush her
in the general.

15:01.968 --> 15:03.534
Ethan?

15:03.536 --> 15:05.169
Get in here!

15:07.274 --> 15:10.108
Would you say we had a problem
with female voters

15:10.110 --> 15:13.978
Yes, sir.
What if we ran
against a female candidate?

15:13.980 --> 15:15.146
Would that be fun for us?

15:15.148 --> 15:16.581
We'd likely get
clobbered, sir.

15:16.583 --> 15:18.116
I will go craft an apology.

15:18.118 --> 15:19.951
Run it by me first.

15:19.953 --> 15:22.587
The prosecution's about to rest.
Now it's our turn.

15:22.589 --> 15:24.956
Your testimony is crucial.
You nail it, we're home free.

15:24.958 --> 15:27.158
Just remember--
supportive, not smug.

15:27.160 --> 15:29.360
I know.
And make just enough eye contact
with the jury.

15:29.362 --> 15:31.095
Too little,
you'll seem impersonal.

15:31.097 --> 15:32.997
Too much,
you'll seem like you're begging.
I appreciate it, shel.

15:32.999 --> 15:36.100
(lowered voice) I have the head
of b.N.C. On the phone.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.568
Tell him I'll call him back.
He said it's urgent.

15:37.570 --> 15:39.537
Something about a story
that's about to break.

15:39.539 --> 15:41.506
He says he wants a comment.
What story?

15:41.508 --> 15:43.441
<i>We met on mixr last week.</i>
<i>It's an app.</i>

15:43.443 --> 15:45.376
<i>People pretend to use it</i>
<i>for networking,</i>

15:45.378 --> 15:47.578
<i>But it's really just</i>
<i>a hookup site.</i>

15:47.580 --> 15:51.182
<i>You know, he has a mole</i>
<i>on his--I mean, it's small,</i>

15:51.184 --> 15:54.152
<i>Anyway, I thought</i>
<i>he was harmless.</i>

15:54.154 --> 16:02.260
<i>I get a text, and it's like...</i>
<i>Whoa! Now I get the name.</i>

16:02.262 --> 16:06.264
She's lying. I've never seen
that girl in my life.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.166
Shelley, you have to
believe me.

16:08.168 --> 16:09.334
Call them up.

16:09.336 --> 16:11.202
Tell them it wasn't me.
Make a statement.

16:11.204 --> 16:13.204
Whatever you have to do.
I did not send that text.

16:13.206 --> 16:15.206
Did you hear what I said?
Harrison.

16:15.208 --> 16:16.541
Give me your phone.
What?

16:16.543 --> 16:20.011
You heard him.
I don't--I left my phone
in the car.

16:20.013 --> 16:22.347
(chuckles)
okay. Me and you,
men's room, now.

16:22.349 --> 16:25.216
You drop trou, and we hope
to god there's no mole.
There's a mole.

16:25.218 --> 16:28.319
(sighs)

16:30.222 --> 16:32.490
I don't know why I...

16:32.492 --> 16:34.325
I have a lot of stress.

16:34.327 --> 16:36.461
I couldn't sleep.

16:36.463 --> 16:39.063
I have a problem, shelley.

16:39.065 --> 16:40.198
Oh, shelley--

16:40.200 --> 16:41.499
Do not touch me.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.501
Not now. Not...

16:43.503 --> 16:47.405
(lowered voice)
don't touch me.

16:48.440 --> 16:50.641
(door opens)

16:50.643 --> 16:52.410
(projector and camera shutter
click)

16:52.412 --> 16:54.645
Honorable discharge
from the navy in '94.

16:54.647 --> 16:58.016
That was the last good thing
to happen to him.

16:58.018 --> 17:01.586
Small airline in florida.
He was fired six months in.

17:01.588 --> 17:04.789
Two marriages.
And a lot of arrests for
drunk and disorderly conduct.

17:04.791 --> 17:09.127
But even those dried up. I'm not
sure how he got by financially.

17:09.129 --> 17:12.163
But she doesn't seem to have
any more money than he did.

17:12.165 --> 17:13.464
What about
the funeral arrangements?

17:13.466 --> 17:15.133
Wherever his sister can find
the cheapest place

17:15.135 --> 17:17.201
To bury a pine box.

17:19.238 --> 17:22.306
(projector and camera shutter
click)

17:31.417 --> 17:33.384
(man) detail, halt!

17:36.455 --> 17:41.159
I never expected all this--
all this pomp and fuss.

17:41.161 --> 17:43.394
(car doors close)

17:44.596 --> 17:47.098
I'm sorry. Can I help you folks?
This is a private service.

17:47.100 --> 17:49.734
Ma'am...

17:49.736 --> 17:52.370
You must be
officer foster's sister.

17:52.372 --> 17:53.771
Marion, is it?

17:53.773 --> 17:55.339
Mr. President?

17:55.341 --> 17:58.309
And tell you
how sorry I am for your loss.

17:58.311 --> 18:00.378
I don't...
Mr. President--

18:00.380 --> 18:01.779
I never met your brother,

18:01.781 --> 18:05.516
But I was in the navy
at the same time.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.351
He was a good man.

18:07.353 --> 18:10.254
I didn't even think he could be
buried here at arlington,

18:10.256 --> 18:15.259
But then veterans affairs
called this morning, and...

18:15.261 --> 18:16.360
Was that you?

18:16.362 --> 18:17.762
Did you do this
for my brother?

18:17.764 --> 18:19.764
They let me pull a few strings
from time to time.

18:19.766 --> 18:21.132
Perk of the job.

18:21.134 --> 18:24.235
But why?

18:24.237 --> 18:26.370
(nina simone's
"wild is the wind" playing)

18:26.372 --> 18:28.406
Pete foster was
an american hero,

18:28.408 --> 18:31.142
And he deserves
to be buried as such.

18:31.144 --> 18:33.678
(man) detail, atten-hut!

18:33.680 --> 18:35.613
Half right... Face!

18:35.615 --> 18:39.484
¶ love me, love me, love me

18:39.486 --> 18:41.552
¶ say you do

18:41.554 --> 18:43.387
Aim! Fire!

18:43.389 --> 18:44.489
(gunshots)

18:44.491 --> 18:45.790
Aim.

18:45.792 --> 18:47.391
Fire.

18:47.393 --> 18:48.893
Aim. Fire.

18:48.895 --> 18:53.698
¶ let me fly away

18:53.700 --> 18:56.434
¶ with you

18:58.504 --> 19:05.543
¶ for my love
is like the wind ¶

19:05.545 --> 19:12.783
¶ and wild is the wind

19:17.856 --> 19:22.593
¶ give me more

19:22.595 --> 19:29.500
¶ than one caress

19:29.502 --> 19:39.877
¶ satisfy this hungriness

19:39.879 --> 19:43.581
¶ let the wind

19:43.583 --> 19:49.754
¶ blow through your heart

19:49.756 --> 19:56.227
¶ for wild is the wind

19:59.831 --> 20:01.599
(sighs)

20:01.601 --> 20:03.434
Are you an idiot, or did
you do it to spite me?

20:03.436 --> 20:05.303
What the hell are you
talking about?

20:05.305 --> 20:08.272
This. The president throws
a funeral

20:08.274 --> 20:09.574
For a down-on-his-luck navy vet,

20:09.576 --> 20:12.743
From the gravedigger's
instagram account?

20:12.745 --> 20:14.579
Me! The chief of staff's
husband,

20:14.581 --> 20:18.382
I could have produced a segment
on the president's heart

20:18.384 --> 20:20.751
At a time when the only organ
people care about is his penis.

20:20.753 --> 20:22.753
But, no, either you didn't
see the potential,

20:22.755 --> 20:24.555
Or--or you didn't see
<i>my</i> potential.

20:24.557 --> 20:26.791
So I ask you again--
are you an idiot,

20:26.793 --> 20:28.559
Or did you do it
to spite me?

20:28.561 --> 20:30.595
James, I had no idea
this was happening.

20:30.597 --> 20:32.930
Really? So the president
calls veterans affairs and says,

20:32.932 --> 20:34.765
"pete foster.
Let's throw him a funeral,"

20:34.767 --> 20:36.968
And no one said a word
to you?
No.

20:36.970 --> 20:38.836
Not everything I do
is a scheme.

20:38.838 --> 20:40.605
You may not believe that,
but it's true.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.674
Okay.
I'm sorry I bothered you.

20:43.676 --> 20:45.910
Wait.

20:45.912 --> 20:48.246
Did you say pete foster?

20:48.248 --> 20:51.315
(indistinct conversations,
children shouting playfully)

20:53.752 --> 20:56.854
You could have given me
a heads-up.
Not exactly my style.

20:56.856 --> 20:59.390
Or, okay, I don't know,
you could have not killed him.

20:59.392 --> 21:02.526
Calm down, cyrus.
Pete foster killed pete foster.

21:02.528 --> 21:04.629
Right, of course. Well,
whatever the official story is,

21:04.631 --> 21:06.597
The president heard about it,
because he went...

21:06.599 --> 21:10.368
<i>He practically arranged</i>
<i>the damn flowers himself.</i>

21:10.370 --> 21:11.769
<i>(rowan) pete foster had</i>
<i>every intention--</i>

21:11.771 --> 21:15.373
(children singing indistinctly,
<i>static hisses)</i>

21:15.375 --> 21:17.441
<i>He had the original</i>
<i>flight plan, cyrus,</i>

21:17.443 --> 21:20.411
And he was gonna use it--
<i>(children singing,</i>
<i>static hissing)</i>

21:20.413 --> 21:22.013
<i>(children continue</i>
<i>singing indistinctly)</i>

21:22.015 --> 21:23.414
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

21:23.416 --> 21:26.751
<i>A loaded gun that I was</i>
<i>not about to let go off.</i>

21:26.753 --> 21:28.486
<i>So taking care of the man?</i>
<i>Necessary.</i>

21:28.488 --> 21:31.322
<i>Giving you a heads-up?</i>
<i>Less so.</i>

21:31.324 --> 21:32.690
<i>(woman) this day</i>
<i>could not have gone worse</i>

21:32.692 --> 21:35.593
<i>(man) the defense,</i>
<i>who we should point out,</i>

21:35.595 --> 21:39.630
<i>How do we think ms. Pope</i>
<i>is feeling right now, anne?</i>

21:39.632 --> 21:41.899
<i>First she's accused of</i>
<i>an affair with the president,</i>

21:41.901 --> 21:45.503
<i>By real mistress</i>
<i>jeannine locke, and now this.</i>

21:45.505 --> 21:47.405
<i>(anne) that's right, tanner,</i>
<i>and let's not forget,</i>

21:47.407 --> 21:48.806
<i>This is a woman</i>
<i>who used to command</i>

21:48.808 --> 21:50.675
<i>A lot of respect</i>
<i>in this town.</i>

21:50.677 --> 21:52.076
<i>Her name alone was enough</i>
<i>to strike fear</i>

21:52.078 --> 21:53.844
<i>Into people's hearts.</i>

21:53.846 --> 21:55.479
<i>(tanner) and now it's close</i>
<i>to becoming a punchline.</i>

21:55.481 --> 21:57.014
(turns tv off)

21:57.016 --> 21:58.749
If you're coming to say
that we need to drop the case,

21:58.751 --> 22:00.618
Don't waste your time.
He lied to us, liv.

22:00.620 --> 22:02.086
And if he lied to us
about the sexting,

22:02.088 --> 22:03.754
Who's to say he's not lying
about killing the girl?

22:03.756 --> 22:05.456
Shelley meyers
is in the wind, gone.

22:05.458 --> 22:06.757
She's not answering
her cell.

22:06.759 --> 22:08.592
She's not at home
or her sister's.

22:08.594 --> 22:09.927
If we jump ship now,
we just look smart.

22:09.929 --> 22:13.731
We can all work for free
just for a few months.

22:13.733 --> 22:15.533
We're not broke yet.
We're fine. I have my savings.

22:15.535 --> 22:18.769
You shouldn't have to use it.
Quitting is not an option.

22:18.771 --> 22:20.738
Harrison, tomorrow morning,

22:20.740 --> 22:22.773
Do whatever you have to do
to stall.

22:22.775 --> 22:26.377
Buy us some time with the judge
until we track shelley down.

22:26.379 --> 22:28.813
Please. Go. Find her.

22:32.918 --> 22:34.685
(sighs)

22:39.458 --> 22:41.792
Bad time?
You shouldn't be here.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.461
Does the name pete foster
mean anything to you?

22:43.463 --> 22:45.129
That's who your father
had huck kill.
What did I tell you?

22:45.131 --> 22:46.664
He was in possession
of something dangerous,

22:46.666 --> 22:47.798
And not just to your father.

22:47.800 --> 22:48.933
To fitz, to the white house.

22:48.935 --> 22:50.101
It was a flight plan
of some kind.

22:50.103 --> 22:51.802
I have no idea
what you're talking about,

22:51.804 --> 22:54.939
Okay. Look.
Pete foster was a pilot.
(file rustling)

22:54.941 --> 22:56.741
He flew 86 missions,
but there are only 85

22:56.743 --> 22:58.075
Listed individually
on his jacket,

22:58.077 --> 22:59.610
Which means that one of them
is missing--

22:59.612 --> 23:01.645
Stop. I have told you
over and over

23:01.647 --> 23:02.980
That I want nothing to do
with this--

23:02.982 --> 23:04.882
What the white house does,
my father--none of it.

23:04.884 --> 23:06.684
So take your files
and your conspiracies

23:06.686 --> 23:09.653
And leave my office. Now.

23:12.425 --> 23:16.160
(projector and camera shutter
clicks)

23:21.700 --> 23:23.067
(door closes)

23:26.938 --> 23:29.607
(door opens and closes)

23:36.047 --> 23:37.581
(clicks switch)

23:39.451 --> 23:42.853
(cyrus) or, okay, I don't know,
<i>you could have not killed him.</i>

23:42.855 --> 23:45.723
<i>(rowan) calm down, cyrus.</i>
<i>Pete foster killed pete foster.</i>

23:45.725 --> 23:48.759
<i>Calm down, cyrus.</i>
<i>Pete foster killed pete foster.</i>
<i>No! (groaning)</i>

23:48.761 --> 23:51.462
(children singing indistinctly)

23:51.464 --> 23:55.533
<i>(child speaks indistinctly)</i>
<i>pete foster had</i>
<i>every intention--</i>

23:55.535 --> 23:58.536
<i>...On grant. A loaded gun that</i>
<i>I was not about to let go off.</i>

23:58.538 --> 24:01.739
<i>He had the original</i>
<i>flight plan, cyrus,</i>

24:01.741 --> 24:07.211
<i>He had the original</i>
<i>flight plan, cyrus.</i>

24:08.447 --> 24:10.080
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

24:11.917 --> 24:13.751
(thud)

24:13.753 --> 24:15.820
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

24:17.956 --> 24:20.825
<i>Pete foster</i>
<i>killed pete foster.</i>

24:21.760 --> 24:24.528
...Left some unfinished
business for you inside.

24:29.569 --> 24:33.571
<i>Of foot-in-mouth disease</i>
<i>from time to time.</i>

24:33.573 --> 24:37.842
<i>First lady apologized.</i>
<i>Apology accepted.</i>

24:37.844 --> 24:39.577
<i>I will say this, though.</i>

24:39.579 --> 24:43.714
(turns off tv
sets down remote control)
a star is born.
You should be so proud.

24:43.716 --> 24:45.649
I apologized.
What more can I do?

24:45.651 --> 24:48.052
You didn't just create a star.
You created a movement.

24:48.054 --> 24:49.920
A movement? Please.

24:49.922 --> 24:52.857
Her favorables are up
12 points in the last 2 days.

24:52.859 --> 24:55.593
(groans)
she's been top 10 on twitter
for the last 48 hours.

24:55.595 --> 24:57.561
And you know what else
is trending?

24:57.563 --> 24:59.263
Hashtag--
"mellie has a big fat mouth--"
leave her alone!

24:59.265 --> 25:02.266
Her apology was gracious.

25:02.268 --> 25:03.868
Sir, with all due respect--
(fitz) enough!

25:03.870 --> 25:05.636
Take a walk, cyrus.

25:07.706 --> 25:09.707
(papers rustle)

25:09.709 --> 25:11.675
(exhales) thank you.

25:11.677 --> 25:13.944
We all make mistakes.

25:23.922 --> 25:25.022
(gasps)

25:29.828 --> 25:31.529
(exhales sharply)

25:31.531 --> 25:33.664
You're going to fly out
to montana right now.

25:33.666 --> 25:34.999
Today!

25:35.001 --> 25:36.834
And you are going to walk
the deserted streets

25:36.836 --> 25:38.969
Of seven forks
or horsefly gulch

25:38.971 --> 25:41.272
Or apache tears or whatever
the hell the name is

25:41.274 --> 25:43.607
Of the hick town
our calamity jane calls home,

25:43.609 --> 25:44.975
And you're going to talk
to everyone

